introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Newport was born in 1213, in Pembrokeshire, Wales. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs William Newport."},"et":{"1213–":"1213–Surnud","1213–Female":"1213–Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1213–Male":"1213–Surnud","1213":"1213","1240":"1240","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1213–":"1213–Kuollut","1213–Female":"1213–Kuollut","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1213–Male":"1213–Kuollut","1213":"1213","1240":"1240","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1213–":"1213–Décédé","1213–Female":"1213–Décédée","1240–Female":"1240–Décédée","1213–Male":"1213–Décédé","1213":"1213","1240":"1240","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Galles","Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"William Newport est né en 1213, à Pembrokeshire, Galles. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs William Newport."},"de":{"1213–":"1213–Verstorben","1213–Female":"1213–Verstorben","1240–Female":"1240–Verstorben","1213–Male":"1213–Verstorben","1213":"1213","1240":"1240","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales","lifeSummary":"William Newport wurde 1213 in Pembrokeshire, Wales geboren. Er hatte mit Mrs William Newport mindestens 1 Tochter."},"h